"``accept`` 方法，可以通过该方法来实现反序列化类白/黑名单控制，一个demo如下"
msgstr ""
"The ``ValidatingObjectInputStream`` class in the Apache Commons IO "
"Serialization package provides the ``accept`` method, which can be used to "
"implement whitelist or blacklist control for deserialized classes. A demo is "
"shown below"

#: ../../source/language/java/unserialize.rst:122
msgid "ObjectInputFilter(JEP290)"
msgstr "ObjectInputFilter(JEP290)"

#: ../../source/language/java/unserialize.rst:123
msgid ""
"Java 9提供了支持序列化数据过滤的新特性，可以继承 ``java.io.ObjectInputFilter`` 类重写 "
"``checkInput`` 方法来实现自定义的过滤器，并使用 ``ObjectInputStream`` 对象的 "
"``setObjectInputFilter`` 设置过滤器来实现反序列化类白/黑名单控制。这个机制本身是针对Java "
"9的一个新特性，但是随后官方突然决定向下引进该增强机制，分别对JDK 6,7,8进行了支持。这个机制主要描述了如下的机制："
msgstr ""
"Java 9 provides a new feature that supports filtering of serialized data. "
"You can extend the ``java.io.ObjectInputFilter`` class, override the "
"``checkInput`` method to implement a custom filter, and use "
"``setObjectInputFilter`` on an ``ObjectInputStream`` object to implement "
"whitelist or blacklist control for deserialized classes. This mechanism was "
"originally a Java 9 feature, but Oracle later decided to backport the "
"enhancement and added support for JDK 6, 7, and 8. The mechanism mainly "
"covers the following:"

#: ../../source/language/java/unserialize.rst:125
msgid "提供一个限制反序列化类的机制，白名单或者黑名单"
msgstr "Provide a mechanism to restrict deserialized classes, either with a whitelist or a blacklist"

#: ../../source/language/java/unserialize.rst:126
msgid "限制反序列化的深度和复杂度"
msgstr "Limit deserialization depth and complexity"

#: ../../source/language/java/unserialize.rst:127
